-- clikae Ghostty launcher. Ghostty's macOS CLI can't open a window directly, so we
-- go through `open -na Ghostty.app --args`. Crucially the command is passed via a
-- TRUSTED config file (--config-file=), NOT via -e: Ghostty pops an
-- "Allow Ghostty to execute …?" confirmation for -e (its guard against an external
-- app injecting a command), so a -e launcher looks like an empty shell until you
-- click Allow. A user config file is trusted → no dialog, and the title sticks.
--
-- The config lives in THIS bundle's Resources, located at runtime via `path to me`
-- so the launcher keeps working if the .app is moved. app.sh writes
-- Contents/Resources/clikae-ghostty.conf (a `title = …` + `command = …` pair) right
-- after compiling this script. This template has no substitution tokens.

on run
    set confPath to (POSIX path of (path to me)) & "Contents/Resources/clikae-ghostty.conf"
    do shell script "open -na Ghostty.app --args --config-file=" & quoted form of confPath
end run
